WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.656
All living things

00:00:01.656 --> 00:00:03.313
need food to

00:00:03.313 --> 00:00:04.969
grow. While animals

00:00:04.969 --> 00:00:06.626
find food, plants

00:00:06.626 --> 00:00:08.283
make their own

00:00:08.283 --> 00:00:09.939
using sunlight.

00:00:09.939 --> 00:00:11.434
Inside plant leaves,

00:00:11.434 --> 00:00:12.928
there is a

00:00:12.928 --> 00:00:14.422
green pigment called

00:00:14.422 --> 00:00:15.917
chlorophyll. It acts

00:00:15.917 --> 00:00:17.411
like a solar

00:00:17.411 --> 00:00:18.905
panel to capture

00:00:18.905 --> 00:00:20.399
light.

00:00:20.399 --> 00:00:22.071
Plants also absorb

00:00:22.071 --> 00:00:23.743
water from the

00:00:23.743 --> 00:00:25.414
soil through roots,

00:00:25.414 --> 00:00:27.086
and pull in

00:00:27.086 --> 00:00:28.758
carbon dioxide gas

00:00:28.758 --> 00:00:30.429
from the air.

00:00:30.429 --> 00:00:32.170
Sunlight splits water

00:00:32.170 --> 00:00:33.910
and gas into

00:00:33.910 --> 00:00:35.650
glucose sugar for

00:00:35.650 --> 00:00:37.390
food, and releases

00:00:37.390 --> 00:00:39.130
clean oxygen for

00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:40.870
us to breathe.

